  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nTons of `Waiting for transaction signature. Please check your wallet for a transaction approval message.` log entries while running unit tests. This makes reading through the results pretty problematic, especially if there are many transactions in your tests or their before/beforeEach hooks.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n- write a smart contract and a test\r\n- commit it to github, to a repository which runs the tests in a github action\r\n- run the test and check the output\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nSee the output of truffle test (mocha).\r\n![output_5 5 6](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6696659/162433951-9c46cd5f-0a4e-4e79-8c1e-b21a4b7feb9b.png)\r\n(screenshot from Truffle 5.5.6)\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nI see not only the usual test output, but \"`Waiting for transaction signature. Please check your wallet for a transaction approval message.`\" entries too.\r\n![output_5 5 8](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6696659/162502025-c40d2461-d142-47fe-aa35-3f43539f2918.png)\r\n(screenshot from Truffle 5.5.8)\r\nNote that a similar issue was present in Truffle 5.5.7 when running locally too, but that was fixed in 5.5.8, thus I edited the issue.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04.3\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache v7.0.4\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.5.8\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 16\r\n\r\n",
